aiLCTrapGtranSwitch.name: aiLCTrapGtranSwitch
aiLCTrapGtranSwitch.description: Trap sent when the GTRAN switches the fiber span utilized by the active laser.

aiLCTrapGbicInserted.name: aiLCTrapGbicInserted
aiLCTrapGbicInserted.description: Trap sent when a Gigabit Ethernet Interface Converter is inserted.

aiLCTrapGbicRemoved.name: aiLCTrapGbicRemoved
aiLCTrapGbicRemoved.description: Trap sent when a Gigabit Ethernet Interface Converter is removed.

aiLCGtranActiveTable.name: aiLCGtranActiveTable
aiLCGtranActiveTable.description: Information on the active laser of the GTRAN module.

aiLCGtranActiveEntry.name: aiLCGtranActiveEntry
aiLCGtranActiveEntry.description: Information on a given GTRAN active laser

aiLCGtranActiveIndex.name: aiLCGtranActiveIndex
aiLCGtranActiveIndex.description: Index of this object in the current table. Since this table entry is an extension of the ifTable, this should object should have the same value as the corresponding ifIndex.

aiLCGtranActiveBackupIndex.name: aiLCGtranActiveBackupIndex
aiLCGtranActiveBackupIndex.description: Index of the corresponding backup laser.

aiLCGtranActiveSpan.name: aiLCGtranActiveSpan
aiLCGtranActiveSpan.description: Indicates which fiber span is currently being utilized by the actvie laser

aiLCGtranActiveRxUtilization.name: aiLCGtranActiveRxUtilization
aiLCGtranActiveRxUtilization.description: Approximate percentage utilization of the fiber. This only accounts for incoming (received) packets.

aiLCGtranActiveTxUtilization.name: aiLCGtranActiveTxUtilization
aiLCGtranActiveTxUtilization.description: Approximate percentage utilization of the fiber. This only accounts for outgoing (transmitted) packets.

aiLCGtranActiveClockSlave.name: aiLCGtranActiveClockSlave
aiLCGtranActiveClockSlave.description: True if this laser is the clock slave.

aiLCGtranActiveCoolerStatus.name: aiLCGtranActiveCoolerStatus
aiLCGtranActiveCoolerStatus.description: The state of the laser cooler. While the cooler can be disabled, this will render the laser ineffective. This object is primarily here for status purposes.

aiLCGtranActiveTemperature.name: aiLCGtranActiveTemperature
aiLCGtranActiveTemperature.description: The GTRAN part is aware when it passes out of its operational temperature range. This object turns to trouble(2) as soon as we get such a report from the GTRAN.

aiLCGtranActiveTxPower.name: aiLCGtranActiveTxPower
aiLCGtranActiveTxPower.description: Output power level. The GTRAN will report under(2) if its self monitoring indicates that the laser is not transmitting at full power. over(3) is not currently used, but included for symmetry.

aiLCGtranBackupIndex.name: aiLCGtranBackupIndex
aiLCGtranBackupIndex.description: Index of this object in the current table. Since this table entry is an extension of the ifTable, this should object should have the same value as the corresponding ifIndex.

aiLCGtranBackupActiveIndex.name: aiLCGtranBackupActiveIndex
aiLCGtranBackupActiveIndex.description: Index of the corresponding active laser.

aiLCGbicIndex.name: aiLCGbicIndex
aiLCGbicIndex.description: Index of this object in the current table. Since this table entry is an extension of the ifTable, this should object should have the same value as the corresponding ifIndex.

aiLCGbicConnectorType.name: aiLCGbicConnectorType
aiLCGbicConnectorType.description: Type of connector in this GBIC slot.

aiLCGbicTxMode.name: aiLCGbicTxMode
aiLCGbicTxMode.description: The true administrative state of this interface. down(1) and up(2) carry the same semantics as ifAdminStatus. gtran(3) is used when this interface should only be operational if the gtran device is capable of passing packets. Note that the test status of the device is not truly orthogonal to this variable and is set separately. However, setting that variable may effect the state of this one.

aiLCGbicRxUtilization.name: aiLCGbicRxUtilization
aiLCGbicRxUtilization.description: Approximate percentage utilization of the fiber. This only accounts for incoming (received) packets.

aiLCGbicTxUtilization.name: aiLCGbicTxUtilization
aiLCGbicTxUtilization.description: Approximate percentage utilization of the fiber. This only accounts for outgoing (transmitted) packets.
